 of the computations against\nroundoff errors and leads to accurate variants of the gradient-based AFs.\nAdditionally, such methods are ideal for simultaneous state estimation and\nparameter identification since all values are computed in parallel. The\nnumerical experiments are given.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 19 Mar 2013 14:39:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 19 Dec 2013 12:00:52 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 30 Dec 2016 14:43:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-02"}
